{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember it was-- must have been about 1936 or '37, somebody introduced a law into the Sejm, which is like the Parliament here, they should forbid the ritual slaughtering, the Shechitah.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as a protest, all Jews stopped buying meat or chickens between Pesach and Shavuot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's a period of about six weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the farmers, which were mainly Poles that used to bring the produce into town, suffered because a third of the population stopped buying meat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So-- also, funnily enough, the people that sold salt also suffered because Jews use salt to salt the meat before they eat it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, it's got to be salted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they couldn't sell much-- the-- the-- the-- the sale of salt dropped because of the bill.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they also suffered.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Finally, this bill was defeated and it never reappeared again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So also, I must say that some of the non-Orthodox Jews tried to buy meat from non-- from non-Jewish shops.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so the Jewish used to stand outside the non-Jewish shops and stop these people from going in to buy the non-kosher meat.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And even the non-Orthodox Jews also stopped these people from going in because to-- they wanted this bill should be defeated as a matter of principle, even if they didn't care whether they have kosher meat or not.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But to-- to know that to be solid-- to have solidarity, they also protested against this-- these people going into the other shops and that also helped for the bill to be defeated.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, to me, this didn't affect me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I was a child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was only in my-- well, I was 10 or-- or nine, depending on when.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When the war broke out, I was 12 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
